      <header>Ebou Dar</header>
      <slot>10</slot>
      <level>203</level>
      <author>315230</author>
      <date>1052833720</date>
      <authorname>Lyeshal</authorname>
      <text>As reported by a messenger from Tuon, leader of the Hailene, Daughter of
the Nine Moons, and heir to the Empress, may she live forever.    

The mission to Amadicia has been successful.  The Ever Victorious Army 
has once again shown the glory of the Empress, may she live forever, and
has taken Amadicia.  There have been casualties, but all died for the glory
of the Empire, and have brought honor to the name of the Empress with their
sacrifices.

Our numbers were as follows:
The Ever Victorious Army consisted of approximately 22,000 of those born
in Seanchan, with an additional 14,000 Oathtakers.  About a third of this
number were our air forces, consisting of the Fists of Heaven, their 
to'raken, and the morat'to'raken.  The remaining two-thirds were our ground
troops, consisting of men on foot, as well as the exotics.  Included in the
exotic forces were approximately 60 damane.  We have lost perhaps as many
as two thousand of our troops.

The troops are moving on Ebou Dar and the Daughter of the Nine Moons is
optimistic that this city will be taken as swiftly as the others.  Once
this is done, our supply routes can be changed to move through this city
by means of the sea, rather than overland from Tarabon as it is now.

The remainder of our forces continue to maintain order in Tarabon and Arad
Doman, with no reinforcements to the main troops being sent at this time.

My words are that of the Lady Tuon, Leader of the Hailene, Daughter of the
Nine Moons, and heir to the Empress, may she live forever, and may I be
dishonored if what I have reported are not her words.
</text>
